rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of the week is going to be even more tame than usual; COVID 19 restrictions are being instituted again so no eating out or visiting my son, etc.  But, hopefully, the weather cooperates and I get to go out and exercise a bit.  Otherwise, I'll reach out to people on the phone and putter around the house as has become the new normal.
critical_positive: I think my conversation partner was very sweet and we are both leaning liberal.  I think we had a good sense of rapport despite being different ages.  There were no problematic moments or lack of understanding between us.  She was so polite, I felt, and politeness always makes for good social flow, even if we hadn't agreed on so many things.
critical_negative: Perhaps because I am older, I think I tend to dominate the conversation.  I don't mean to do this.  In part, counter-intuitively, it's because I do have some social anxiety and I overcompensate; but, also, I wonder if it is an unthinking, subconscious reaction to being the older person in the conversation.  If it is, I don't like that in myself because in my "known mind" I believe all ages and segments of the population have a lot to learn from each other and we should all respect each other.

rest_of_day_open: I will probably study and work mainly, and spend time with my partner. I may visit a friend as we hang out at least once a week. I'm really trying hard to finish a certain section of schoolwork though, so that will be the main focus. We are also trying to buy a car.
critical_positive: We had similar previous professions, and I worked with people with developmental disabilities and her son has autism. We also seemed to agree on a lot of political topics, and were able to discuss our concerns with COVID-19 for a while. She was very kind and seemed like she cared a lot about others.
critical_negative: I believe I am a lot more left-wing than she is, so I had to hold my tongue a bit when we were discussing abortion rights. She was also older than I am, so I feel like we didn't share certain life experiences and had a bit of a generational gap.
